Task 1:
Version control is essential for collaborative software development, offering benefits such as history tracking, collaboration support, conflict resolution, traceability, and accountability. 
It enables teams to work concurrently on different branches, merge changes seamlessly.
Version control systems also play a critical role in modern development practices, facilitating continuous integration and deployment. With features like branching and merging, pull request etc.
version control ensures a structured and efficient approach to managing code, enhancing collaboration, and maintaining code quality over time.
